    "input": {
      "base": "main",
      "body": "## Summary\n\nThis pull request introduces a comprehensive pull-request automation workflow for the Node.js project. It adds `.github/workflows/pr-automation.yml`, which runs on `pull_request` events for `opened`, `synchronize`, and `reopened` activity.\n\n## Workflow jobs\n\nAll jobs are defined independently with no `needs` dependencies, so GitHub Actions can run them in parallel:\n\n1. **code-quality**\n   - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`\n   - Runs ESLint with `npm run lint`\n   - Runs Prettier formatting checks\n   - Posts a PR comment containing `Code Quality Report`, `ESLint`, and `Prettier`\n\n2. **testing-suite**\n   - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`\n   - Runs the full test suite with `npm test` and coverage enabled\n   - Posts a PR comment containing `Test Coverage Report`\n   - Uploads coverage artifacts for review\n\n3. **security-scan**\n   - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`\n   - Runs dependency vulnerability checks with `npm audit`\n   - Scans changed files for common secret patterns\n   - Posts a PR comment containing `Security Scan Report`, `Vulnerabilities`, and `Dependencies`\n\n4. **build-validation**\n   - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`\n   - Runs the application build\n   - Starts the app and validates key endpoints\n   - Creates and uploads deployment preview artifacts\n   - Posts a PR comment containing `Build Validation`\n\n## Reliability and safety notes\n\n- Each reporting step uses an idempotent marker comment and updates the existing report comment on subsequent pushes instead of creating duplicates.\n- Validation commands capture logs and publish clear summaries to PR comments.\n- Jobs collect reports before enforcing gates, so contributors receive actionable feedback even when a check fails.\n- The workflow avoids cross-job dependencies to preserve parallel execution.\n- GitHub Script variables use job-specific names to avoid identifier conflicts.",
