      "result": "{\"meta\": null, \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\\"id\\\":3990433206,\\\"number\\\":1,\\\"state\\\":\\\"open\\\",\\\"locked\\\":false,\\\"title\\\":\\\"Implement Pull Request Automation Workflow\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"## Summary\\\\n\\\\nThis pull request introduces a comprehensive pull-request automation workflow for the Node.js project. It adds `.github/workflows/pr-automation.yml`, which runs on `pull_request` events for `opened`, `synchronize`, and `reopened` activity.\\\\n\\\\n## Workflow jobs\\\\n\\\\nAll jobs are defined independently with no `needs` dependencies, so GitHub Actions can run them in parallel:\\\\n\\\\n1. **code-quality**\\\\n   - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`\\\\n   - Runs ESLint with `npm run lint`\\\\n   - Runs Prettier formatting checks\\\\n   - Posts a PR comment containing `Code Quality Report`, `ESLint`, and `Prettier`\\\\n\\\\n2. **testing-suite**\\\\n   - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`\\\\n   - Runs the full test suite with `npm test` and coverage enabled\\\\n   - Posts a PR comment containing `Test Coverage Report`\\\\n   - Uploads coverage artifacts for review\\\\n\\\\n3. **security-scan**\\\\n   - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`\\\\n   - Runs dependency vulnerability checks with `npm audit`\\\\n   - Scans changed files for common secret patterns\\\\n   - Posts a PR comment containing `Security Scan Report`, `Vulnerabilities`, and `Dependencies`\\\\n\\\\n4. **build-validation**\\\\n   - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`\\\\n   - Runs the application build\\\\n   - Starts the app and validates key endpoints\\\\n   - Creates and uploads deployment preview artifacts\\\\n   - Posts a PR comment containing `Build Validation`\\\\n\\\\n## Reliability and safety notes\\\\n\\\\n- Each reporting step uses an idempotent marker comment and updates the existing report comment on subsequent pushes instead of creating duplicates.\\\\n- Validation commands capture logs and publish clear summaries to PR comments.\\\\n- Jobs collect reports before enforcing gates, so contributors receive actionable feedback even when a check fails.\\\\n- The workflow avoids cross-job dependencies to preserve parallel execution.\\\\n- GitHub Script variables use job-specific names to avoid identifier conflicts.\\\",\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T11:42:27Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T11:42:49Z\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/followers\\\",\\\"gists_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/gists{/gist_id}\\\",\\\"organizations_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/orgs\\\",\\\"received_events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/received_events\\\",\\\"repos_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/repos\\\",\\\"starred_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/starred{/owner}{/repo}\\\",\\\"subscriptions_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/subscriptions\\\"},\\\"draft\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/mcpmark-cicd/pulls/1\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud/mcpmark-cicd/pull/1\\\",\\\"issue_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/mcpmark-cicd/issues/1\\\",\\\"statuses_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/mcpmark-cicd/statuses/33e63ee1524df2c67b0306dd3b2ab